DEG analysis with EdgeR

Pablo L. Cardozo

2024-07-04

This document describes the main coding steps used in this work to remove batch effects using RUV-seq (residuals method), followed by EdgeR differential gene expression analysis.

Removing batch effects with RUV-seq

Since whole blood was drawn from the same individual at different time points, batch effects were removed to avoid unwanted artifacts in our transcriptomic analysis. For that, we used the RUV-seq package, parsing the residuals method and k = 5, according to the package vignette instructions.

set <- newSeqExpressionSet(as.matrix(count_data),
                           phenoData = data.frame(samples$group, row.names = colnames(count_data)))

set <- betweenLaneNormalization(set, which = "upper")

# According to Risso et al 2014, RUVr does not require an empirical set of
# housekeeping genes. As suggested by them, all genes can be passed as
# arguments in the RUVr function and it will work as usual.

genes <- rownames(counts(set))
x <- pData(set)[, 1]

design <- model.matrix(~0+x, data = pData(set))
y <- DGEList(counts = counts(set), group = x)
y <- normLibSizes(y, method = "TMM")
y <- estimateGLMCommonDisp(y, design)
y <- estimateGLMTagwiseDisp(y, design)
fit <- glmFit(y, design)
res <- residuals(fit, type = "deviance")
ruvr_model <- RUVr(set, genes, k = 5, res)

# Create table with normalized and batch-effects removed counts 
write.table(normCounts(ruvr_model), 'normCounts_RUV.csv', sep = '\t', quote = F)

EdgeR for Differential Gene Expression Analysis

After removing batch effects, we carried out differential gene expression analysis using EdgeR. To make sure batch effects were removed in this analysis, each RUV-seq co-variate was included in the matrix model.

new_set <- newSeqExpressionSet(as.matrix(count_data),
                               phenoData = data.frame(samples$group, row.names = colnames(count_data)))

#Assigning covariates from RUV-seq

W1 <- ruvr_model$W_1
W2 <- ruvr_model$W_2
W3 <- ruvr_model$W_3
W4 <- ruvr_model$W_4
W5 <- ruvr_model$W_5

group_data <- pData(new_set)[, 1]

new_design <- model.matrix(~0+W1+W2+W3+W4+W5+group_data, group = group_data)
dge <- DGEList(counts = counts(new_set), group = group_data)
dge <- normLibSizes(dge, method = "TMM")
dge <- estimateDisp(dge, new_design)

#Determining DEGs between groups (contrasts)

new_fit <- glmFit(dge, new_design, robust = T)

my_contrasts <- makeContrasts(HCP_tnf_vs_HCP_ns = group_datahcp_tnf - group_datahcp_ns, SCZ_ns_vs_HCP_ns = group_datascz_ns - group_datahcp_ns,       SCZ_tnf_vs_HCP_ns = group_datascz_tnf - group_datahcp_ns, levels = new_design)

gene_annot <- as.data.frame(rownames(count_table))

colnames(gene_annot) <- 'ENSEMBL'

dictionary <- getBM(attributes = c('ensembl_gene_id', 'hgnc_symbol'),
                    filters = 'ensembl_gene_id', values = gene_annot$ENSEMBL,
                    mart = db_homo_s, uniqueRows = F, useCache = T)

gene_annot <- left_join(gene_annot, dictionary, by = join_by('ENSEMBL' == 'ensembl_gene_id'),
                        multiple = 'first') %>% relocate(hgnc_symbol, .after = ENSEMBL)

colnames(gene_annot) <- c('ENSEMBL', 'SYMBOL')
gene_annot$SYMBOL[is.na(gene_annot$SYMBOL)] <- ''

Creating Tables and Figures from DEG analysis results

The function below was used to generate results table, volcano plot figures and also .rnk files for further Gene-set enrichment analysis.

# Function to create tables, figures and rnk files

DEG_function <- function(fit, cont, gene_list){
  
  for (i in colnames(cont)){
    res <- assign(paste0('DEG_', i), glmLRT(fit, contrast = cont[,i]), pos = .GlobalEnv)
    res$table$SignedRank <- sign(res$table$logFC) * (-log10(res$table$PValue))
    res$table$Gene_Symbol <- gene_annot$SYMBOL[match(rownames(res$table), gene_annot$ENSEMBL)]
    res$table$Gene_Symbol[is.na(res$table$Gene_Symbol)] <- ''
    res <- topTags(res, n = Inf, sort.by = 'PValue')
    res$table$FDR[is.na(res$table$FDR)] = 1
    saveRDS(res, file = paste0('DEG_', i, '.rds'))
    res <- as.data.frame(res$table[order(res$table$FDR),]) %>% relocate(Gene_Symbol, .before = logFC)

# Create summarized table for sig and non-sig genes
    
    if (match(i, colnames(cont)) == 1){
      summary_deg <- data.frame(summary(decideTestsDGE(get(paste0('DEG_', i)), adjust.method = 'BH',
                                                      p.value = 0.05, lfc = 0.5)))
      
      column_df <- c(i)}
    
    else {
      new_summary <- data.frame(summary(decideTestsDGE(get(paste0('DEG_', i)), adjust.method = 'BH',
                                                       p.value = 0.05, lfc = 0.5)))
      
      summary_deg <- rbind(summary_deg, new_summary)
      column_df <- c(column_df, i)
    }
     
# Create RNK file for GSEA PreRanked in ClusterProfiler    
    RNK_df <- data.frame(res[,6], row.names = rownames(res))
    write.table(RNK_df, file = paste0('GSEA_PreRanked_', i, '.rnk'), sep = '\t', quote = F, col.names = F)

# Create DEG Table       
    DEG_df <- res[,c(1:5,7)]
    write.table(DEG_df, file = paste0('DEG_edgeR_', i, '.csv'), sep = '\t', quote = F)
    
    # Volcano plot
    
    res <- res %>% mutate(
      color = case_when(logFC >= 0.5 & FDR < 0.05 ~ 'Upregulated',
                        logFC <= -0.5 & FDR < 0.05 ~ 'Downregulated',
                        TRUE ~ 'Unchanged'))
    
    res <- res %>% mutate(
      FC_coord = case_when(abs(logFC) > 5 ~ sign(logFC)*5,
                           TRUE ~ logFC))
    
    res <- res %>% mutate(
      FDR_coord = case_when(-log10(FDR) > 30 ~ 1e-30,
                            TRUE ~ FDR))
    
    res <- res %>% mutate(
      point = case_when(-log10(FDR) > 30 & abs(logFC) <= 5 ~ as.integer(-9650),
                        -log10(FDR) < 30 & logFC > 5 ~ as.integer(-9658),
                        -log10(FDR) < 30 & logFC < -5 ~ as.integer(-9668),
                        -log10(FDR) > 30 & logFC > 5 ~ as.integer(-9701),
                        -log10(FDR) > 30 & logFC < -5 ~ as.integer(-9700),
                        TRUE ~ as.integer(19)))
    
    volcano <- ggplot(res, aes(logFC, -log10(FDR), label = Gene_Symbol)) +
      geom_point(data = subset(res, point > 0), aes(color = color), alpha = 0.7, size = 2) +
      geom_hline(yintercept = -log10(0.05), linetype = 'dashed', color = 'grey30', linewidth = 1) +
      geom_vline(xintercept = c(-0.5,0.5), linetype = 'dashed', color = 'grey30', linewidth = 1) +
      ggtitle(substr(i, 1, nchar(i))) + coord_cartesian(xlim = c(-5,5), ylim = c(0,30)) +
      xlab(expression('log'[2]*' FC')) + ylab(expression('-log'[10]*' (p-adj)')) +
      scale_color_manual(values = c('dodgerblue', 'grey', 'firebrick'))+
      theme_prism() + theme(axis.title.x = element_text(family = 'sans', face = 'plain',
                                                        size = 14),
                            axis.title.y = element_text(family = 'sans', face = 'plain',
                                                        size = 14),
                            axis.text = element_text(family = 'sans', color = 'black', size = 12, face = 'bold'),
                            axis.line = element_line(linewidth = 1),
                            legend.text = element_text(family = 'sans', face = 'plain', size = 12),
                            legend.title = element_text(family = 'sans', face = 'bold', size = 14)) +
      scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(-5,5,1), guide = guide_prism_minor()) + 
      scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0,30,3), guide = guide_prism_minor()) +
      guides(colour = guide_legend(title = 'Expression', override.aes = list(size = 2))) +
      geom_point(data = subset(res, point < 0), aes (x = FC_coord, y = -log10(FDR_coord), color = color, shape = point),
                 size = 3) + scale_shape_identity() +
      geom_text_repel(data = subset(res, res$Gene_Symbol %in% gene_list & (abs(res$logFC) >= 0.5 & res$FDR < 0.05)), size = 3.5, family = 'sans', color = 'black',
                      force = 2, max.overlaps = Inf, xlim = c(-5,5), ylim = c(0,31), min.segment.length = unit(Inf, 'mm'))
    
    ggsave(paste0('DEG_', i, '.tiff'), plot = volcano, device = 'tiff',
           width = 250, height = 150, units = 'mm', compression = 'lzw')
          
  }
  
  summary_deg <- acast(summary_deg, Var1~Var2, value.var = 'Freq')
  colnames(summary_deg) <- column_df
  
  write.table(summary_deg, file = 'summarized_DEGs.csv', sep = '\t', quote = F)
}

Principal component analysis

PCA analysis was carried out using RUV-seq normalized gene count matrix.

p <- pca(as.matrix(log(normCounts(ruvr_model))), metadata = pData(new_set), removeVar = 0.1, scale = TRUE)

tiff('Multiple_PCA_plot_all_groups.tiff', width = 225, height = 100, unit = 'mm',
     res = 600, compression = 'lzw')

pairsplot(p, components = getComponents(p, c(1,2,3)), colby = colnames(p$metadata),
          colkey = c('hcp_ns'='#69b9f5', 'hcp_tnf'='#0b5394', 'scz_ns'='#fd9d9d', 'scz_tnf'='#e50000'),
          pointSize = 2, plotaxes = TRUE, hline = 0, vline = 0, legendPosition = 'top',
          legendLabSize = 8, legendIconSize = 4, axisLabSize = 10, shapekey = 21,
          ncol = 3, nrow = 1, triangle = FALSE, title = 'PCAs of iMGs incubated with ACMs',
          titleLabSize = 12, ylabhjust = 1.3, xlabvjust = 1.5)

We also used the following code to calculate the transcriptional age of our samples.

# Transcriptional age calculations

chrono_age <- data.frame(samples = colnames(norm_counts_data), chrono_age = 45)

age_calc <- predict_age(norm_counts_data, tissue = 'brain', exprtype = 'counts', idtype = 'ENSEMBL',
                        signature = 'GTExAge', stype = 'all', chronage = chrono_age)

age_calc$var1 <- 'Sample'
age_calc$var2 <- 'Mean'

age_calc$sample_gap <- age_calc$RNAAge - mean(age_calc$RNAAge[1:3])

age_calc$mean_gap <- 0
age_calc$mean_gap[1:3] <- mean(age_calc$RNAAge[1:3]) - mean(age_calc$RNAAge[1:3])
age_calc$mean_gap[4:6] <- mean(age_calc$RNAAge[4:6]) - mean(age_calc$RNAAge[1:3])
age_calc$mean_gap[7:9] <- mean(age_calc$RNAAge[7:9]) - mean(age_calc$RNAAge[1:3])
age_calc$mean_gap[10:12] <- mean(age_calc$RNAAge[10:12]) - mean(age_calc$RNAAge[1:3])

age_calc$groups <- rep(c('hct_ns', 'hct_tnf', 'scz_ns', 'scz_tnf'), each = 3)
age_calc$diagnostic <- rep(c('hct', 'scz'), each = 6)
age_calc$stimulation <- rep(c('ns', 'tnf'), each = 3, times = 2)

plot_age_calc <- ggplot(age_calc, aes(fill = groups, color = groups)) + 
  geom_point(aes(x = mean_gap, y = var2), size = 5, shape = 23, color = 'black', stroke = 1) +
  geom_point(aes(x = sample_gap, y = var1), size = 4, shape = 21) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c('hct_ns'='#69b9f5', 'hct_tnf'='#0b5394', 'scz_ns'='#fd9d9d', 'scz_tnf'='#e50000')) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c('hct_ns'='#69b9f5', 'hct_tnf'='#0b5394', 'scz_ns'='#fd9d9d', 'scz_tnf'='#e50000')) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(-2,9,1), guide = guide_prism_minor()) + 
  xlab('Age gap (relative to ACM HCT (N.S.))') + ylab('') +
  theme_prism() + theme(axis.title.x = element_text(family = 'sans', face = 'plain',
                                                    size = 12),
                        axis.text = element_text(family = 'sans', color = 'black', size = 11, face = 'bold'),
                        axis.line.x = element_line(linewidth = 1),
                        axis.line.y = element_blank(), axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
                        legend.text = element_text(family = 'sans', face = 'plain', size = 11),
                        legend.title = element_blank(), legend.key.size = unit(4, 'mm'),
                        panel.grid.major.y = element_line(color = 'grey95', linewidth = 10))

anova_age <- aov(sample_gap ~ diagnostic*stimulation, data = age_calc)
emmean_age <- emmeans(anova_age, ~ diagnostic*stimulation, adjust = 'sidak')
pwcomp_age <- cld(emmean_age, adjust = 'sidak', Letters = letters)

ggsave('RNAAgeCalc.pdf', plot = plot_age_calc, height = 1.6)
